But I've also come to realize that the things that bring ultimate meaning to our lives

235
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,140
are truly unexplainable,

236
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:33,250
that things like that are always beyond the safe, settled reaches of the predictable.

237
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:36,590
And the man who said that was Calvin Miller, and I agree with him.

238
00:17:37,470 --> 00:17:44,090
That there are mysteries that give our life meaning that are beyond completely understanding in our rational mind.

239
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:47,580
And I'm becoming okay with that.

240
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:51,650
Because mystery is still in the heart of faith.

241
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:58,040
And I want us to enter this story with a rational thought, but also with an element of mystery.

242
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:03,560
I want the miracle of Jesus' birth not just to be interesting, but let it tingle your spine.

243
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:09,660
Let God's coming to earth as a human being take your breath away.

244
00:18:10,610 --> 00:18:11,370
That is a miracle.

245
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:17,660
Let the mystery of Jesus' birth and life and death and resurrection

246
00:18:17,660 --> 00:18:21,880
give you hope in the inner recesses of your soul.

247
00:18:25,060 --> 00:18:26,820
When God comes a-knocking at your door,

248
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:32,300
I want you to submit to the mysteries of God and to say something like this,

249
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:38,290
I am the Lord's servant, and I am willing to accept whatever He wants.

250
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:43,560
May everything you've said come true, Mary.

251
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:49,200
Because I've also seen this.

252
00:18:50,220 --> 00:18:56,730
When the most ordinary people say, Lord, may you have your way, great things happen.

253
00:18:57,010 --> 00:19:04,480
When ordinary people say, Lord, do what you will, we'll follow you, churches are born.

254
00:19:06,090 --> 00:19:13,210
When ordinary people say, Lord, I'm your servant, I'm willing to accept whatever may be, ministries grow.

255
00:19:14,770 --> 00:19:18,210
When ordinary people say, Lord, may it be according to your will,

256
00:19:18,570 --> 00:19:20,730
hospitals are born and rise.

257
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:22,950
Christian universities take off.

258
00:19:23,270 --> 00:19:28,030
Visions get implanted and people stretch and do amazing and miraculous things

259
00:19:28,030 --> 00:19:29,670
through the power of God.

260
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:34,560
Some of the greatest missionaries were born when a timid believer said,

261
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,500
I am the Lord's servant.

262
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:41,940
Will you say the same?

263
00:19:42,300 --> 00:19:48,070
Do you embrace the mystery of God this holiday season?

264
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:53,070
Do you embrace the mystery of God in every season?

265
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:59,040
See, our God is a God of serendipities, of doing new things.

266
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:06,460
Often at times we least expect Him, and He breaks forth and does something amazing.

267
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:12,240
He's a God of meekness, of miracles, and mystery.

268
00:20:14,260 --> 00:20:15,840
And I want to ask, will you worship Him?

269
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:17,680
Will you follow Him?

270
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,150
Will you embrace Him and His plan for you?

271
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:30,090
And what I really want this season is not to be obsessed with the trappings and the packaging of the season.

272
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:36,440
I want you to be obsessed with the baby and the risen Lord.

273
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:43,610
And I have avoided the mall this far, thank God.

274
00:20:45,340 --> 00:20:47,520
But I found out I've forgotten one gift.

275
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:52,900
So I still have to enter into the chaos of this week.

276
00:20:55,010 --> 00:20:56,030
And some of you do too.

277
00:20:56,710 --> 00:21:02,810
And I don't want that to somehow crowd the mystery of our God.

278
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:06,860
And I'm going to encourage you as we sing another song here,

279
00:21:06,860 --> 00:21:10,300
and just if you can get away quietly and read this text again,

280
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:14,760
and let the truth and the reality of this story enter your soul

281
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:16,160
in a way you've never allowed it to happen.

282
00:21:17,230 --> 00:21:19,870
Because our God is meek and identifies with our world.

283
00:21:20,670 --> 00:21:23,290
And He does miracles in our life and can do them in yours.

284
00:21:24,980 --> 00:21:25,740
And He's awesome.

285
00:21:27,010 --> 00:21:27,790
And He's mysterious.

286
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:31,260
and that appeals to a part of our soul.

287
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:35,320
It's beyond explainable, but it's very good.

288
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:38,560
And I want you to enter in and say, Lord, thank you.

289
00:21:38,620 --> 00:21:40,860
I'll worship you, and I'll follow you,

290
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,720
and I'll be all about what you want me to be about.

291
00:21:44,390 --> 00:21:46,410
And so I want you to embrace the miracle of Christmas

292
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,520
from a new angle this year,

293
00:21:49,490 --> 00:21:51,350
and may your worship be full and fruitful

294
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:53,340
and blessed and wonderful.

295
00:21:54,610 --> 00:21:55,950
So with that, let me pray for you.

296
00:21:56,880 --> 00:22:01,660
Our Father, I thank you for this wonderful group of people

297
00:22:01,660 --> 00:22:04,600
that you brought from a variety of places this morning

298
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:09,150
to think about and to experience the story once again.

299
00:22:10,570 --> 00:22:12,290
And I pray that your spirit would speak truth

300
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:14,130
and would prick our hearts and our consciences

301
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:16,570
and make it real and alive for us.

302
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:18,250
Pierce our doubts.

303
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,380
Help us, Lord, to embrace the truth

304
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:25,710
and yet to hold it loosely because it is mysterious.

305
00:22:26,190 --> 00:22:26,970
It's beyond us.

306
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:31,480
But help us, Father, to engage who you are,

307
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:35,610
why you came, and what it's all about.

308
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:41,320
Father, I pray this congregation would have a wonderful Christmas experience

309
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:44,560
and enjoy the mysteries of the season.

310
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:50,360
So fill them, Father, with your love and your truth and your passion,

311
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:53,350
and may they have a blessed celebration.

312
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:56,210
In Jesus' name, amen.

313
00:22:56,890 --> 00:22:58,090
We're going to sing Isn't He?

314
00:22:58,310 --> 00:23:00,610
Beautiful, wonderful, counselor, mighty God.

315
00:23:00,610 --> 00:23:01,570
I invite you to stand.

